Hello friend, thanks for checking in. My dad is doing fine and on the long recovery path. Honestly, we’re lucky he’s in the state he is in and not worse. 

He fell through an open hole in the floor on a on-site and fractured all of his ribs on the left hand side of his body (front and back) as well as his clavicle so he fell in the best way possible. There’s still bleeding in his chest cavity but the chest tube should be removed tomorrow or the day after. 

We’re just incredibly fortune he didn’t need surgery to stop the bleeding, broke his back or hit his head harder. He truly dodged a bullet

It’s been a very long few days but the worst is well behind us. He was just moved out of the ICU about an hour ago. 

At the moment we don’t need anything but thanks for reaching out, I appreciate you. 🙏
